public static enum CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinSoftwareUpdateStatus
extends Enum<CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinSoftwareUpdateStatus>

The list of possible status messages when initiating an update of the PayPal integrated Chip & Pin card reader.

Enum Constant Summary
DownloadInProgress
          Download is in progress for the software update
FetchingTerminalKeys
          Indicates we are fetching the keys from the terminal as we prepare to inject new encryption keys
InstallInProgress
          Software update files must be available - we are now installing these
KeyInjectionFailedUnknownError
          Indicates that the key injection failed due to an unknown error
KeyInjectionFailedWithCause
          Indicates that the key injection failed.
KeyInjectionInProgress
          Indicates that the key injection update is in progress
NotYetImplemented
          Your friendly neighborhood SDK dev is working on this one.
RestartingTerminal
          Indicates the terminal being restarted during the software update.
SoftwareUpdateFailedUnknownError
          Indicates that the software update failed due to an unknown error
SoftwareUpdateFailedWithCause
          Indicates that the software update failed.
SoftwareUpdateInProgress
          Indicates that the software update is in progress
UpdatedAndReady
          Device is connected and the software is updated - you are all set to begin taking payments with this reader.
